C%20I%20struggled.%20I%20kept%20re-enlisting%2C%20and%20in%202008%2C%20I%20had%20my%20ongoing%20undiagnosed%20dysphoria.%20Because%20I%20couldn't%20be%20honest%20with%20my%20doctors%20at%20the%20time%2C%20they%20diagnosed%20it%20as%20a%20depressive%20disorder%20and%20attempted%20to%20treat%20it%20as%20such%2C%20unfortunately%2C%20not%20very%20successfully.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20ended%20up%20having%20a%20brief%20hospital%20stay%20after%20some%20pretty%20strong%20suicidal%20ideation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20talking%20to%20the%20doctor%20and%20opening%20up%2C%20to%20what%20extent%20I%20could%2C%20about%20the%20way%20I%20felt%20about%20being%20male.%20The%20doctor%20was%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BDo%20you%20think%20you%20could%20be%20trans%3F%26quot%3B%20My%20answer%20at%20the%20time%20was%20%26quot%3BNo.%26quot%3B%20The%20doctor%20asked%2C%20%26quot%3BWhy%20not%3F%26quot%3B%20And%20I%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20if%20I%20say%20yes%2C%20I%20lose%20everything.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20gave%20me%20some%20antidepressants%20and%20some%20coping%20mechanisms%20for%20dealing%20with%20the%20generalities%20of%20suicidality.%20That%20was%20able%20to%20at%20least%20get%20me%20back%20on%20my%20feet.%20I%20started%20being%20more%20successful%20in%20the%20Army%20after%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20really%20dove%20headfirst%20into%20service%20as%20an%20identity%20and%20trying%20to%20overcome%20my%20feelings%20of%20self-loathing%20and%20all%20the%20symptoms%20of%20dysphoria.%20If%20the%20Army%20says%20that%20all%20I%20need%20to%20do%20is%20follow%20these%20orders%20and%20exhibit%20these%20values%20and%20be%20honest%20and%20selfless%20and%20dedicated%2C%20then%20I%20can%20do%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20mid-%20to%20late%202013%2C%20I%20deployed%20to%20Iraq%2C%20and%20when%20you%20are%20not%20actively%20engaged%20in%20the%20mission%2C%20you%20just%20sit%20in%20your%20containerized%20housing%20unit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20to%20myself%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20to%20think%20about%20my%20life.%20I%20was%20not%20anywhere%20near%20actual%20fighting%2C%20but%20I%20was%20in%20earshot%20of%20things%20and%20thinking%3A%20%26quot%3BIs%20this%20the%20life%20I%20can%20continue%20living%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20writing%20in%20a%20journal%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20I%20am%20transgender.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20back%20from%20Iraq%20on%20Christmas%20Day%202013.%20My%20ex%20and%20I%20had%20been%20married%20for%20a%20decade.%20We%20had%20two%20kids%20together.%20I%20told%20her%20none%20of%20the%20stuff%20that%20I'd%20been%20trying%20to%20do%20had%20worked%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20think%20that%20it%20was%20depression.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20thinking%20I'm%20trans%2C%20and%20after%20a%20couple%20of%20long%20conversations%2C%20it%20came%20down%20to%20her%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20sorry%2C%20but%20I'm%20straight.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226899c5aa-4c27-42de-8922-84fc548c8a54%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMoving%20pretty%20quickly%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22748%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Cathrine%20Schmid%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6650ba5520abc1efe8fd6dba%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22561%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPreparing%20for%20a%20training%20event%20in%202021%3Cp%3EPhoto%20courtesy%20of%20Cathrine%20Schmid%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20ended%20up%20getting%20a%20divorce%2C%20she%20took%20the%20kids%20and%20went%20back%20home%20to%20Oregon%20where%20we%20had%20basically%20grown%20up%20and%20went%20to%20high%20school%20and%20everything%20together.%20She's%20still%20a%20very%2C%20very%20close%20friend%2C%20but%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20what%20I%20had%20at%20the%20time%20was%20completely%20unsustainable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20ended%20up%20climbing%20over%20the%20rail%20on%20the%20Tampa%20Bay%20Bridge%20in%20March%202014.%20Instead%20of%20jumping%2C%20though%2C%20I%20called%20Military%20OneSource%20and%20talked%20to%20one%20of%20their%20counselors%2C%20and%20I%20remember%20saying%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20die%20but%20I%20can't%20live%20like%20this.%20They%20convinced%20me%20to%20go%20back%20to%20the%20hospital.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20the%20Army%20regulations%20still%20had%20%26quot%3Btransgenderism%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20was%20written%20as%20something%20that%20was%20incompatible%20with%20military%20service.%20The%20doctor%20said%20that%20as%20an%20Army%20doctor%2C%20his%20hands%20were%20tied.%20He%20had%20to%20inform%20my%20chain%20of%20command%20because%20I%20had%20a%20diagnosis%20of%20gender%20dysphoria%20and%20the%20Army%20regulations%20said%20that%20he%20had%20to%20tell%20them%20of%20any%20diagnosis%20that%20could%20impact%20my%20eligibility%20for%20continued%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20options%20I%20had%20were%20to%20let%20the%20doctor%20inform%20my%20command%20or%20to%20simply%20out%20myself.%20I%20chose%20to%20out%20myself.%20I%20wrote%20a%20memo%2C%20signed%20it%2C%20and%20basically%20said%2C%20I%20wish%20this%20to%20be%20entered%20into%20the%20official%20record.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20threw%20myself%20at%20the%20mercy%20of%20my%20chain%20of%20command%20and%20said%2C%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20get%20kicked%20out%2C%20I%20promise%20I%20won't%20pursue%20any%20transition%20unless%20authorized%20to%20do%20so%20in%20writing.%20I'm%20getting%20help%20from%20the%20doctors.%20Here's%20my%20record%2C%20and%20here's%20the%20evidence%20that%20I'm%20good%20at%20my%20job%20and%20that%20benefits%20the%20unit.%20Please%20don't%20kick%20me%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20command%20decided%20to%20retain%20me.%20The%20commander's%20guidance%20at%20the%20time%20was%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BOkay%2C%20I'm%20not%20going%20to%20pursue%20separation%20for%20this%2C%20but%20keep%20your%20nose%20clean%20because%20the%20reason%20I'm%20retaining%20you%20is%20because%20you're%20a%20benefit%20to%20this%20formation.%20If%20you%20stop%20being%20a%20benefit%20to%20this%20formation%2C%20then%20I%20will%20not%20be%20able%20to%20justify%20this%20decision%20any%20further.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20doing%20everything%20in%20his%20legal%20authority%20to%20not%20end%20my%20career%2C%20and%20there%20were%20some%20individuals%20in%20the%20unit%20who%20weren't%20pleased%20with%20the%20command's%20decision.%20There%20were%20some%20people%20who%20were%20trying%20to%20find%20reasons%20for%20the%20command%20to%20not%20back%20me%20anymore.%20For%20the%20next%2018%20months%20or%20so%20I%20was%20living%20in%20absolute%20scrutiny%20like%20daily%20haircut%20inspections%2C%20just%20to%20try%20and%20build%20a%20case%20that%20I%20have%20some%20kind%20of%20pattern%20of%20lacking%20adherence%20to%20standards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20a%20couple%20of%20supervisors%20who%20supported%20me%2C%20who%20stood%20up%20for%20me%2C%20and%20who%20helped%20me%20going%20through%20that%20period%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20recently%20receiving%20an%20Army%20equal%20opportunity%20award%2C%20I%20called%20attention%20to%20the%20commander%20I%20had%20a%20decade%20ago%20and%20said%20that%20he%20saved%20my%20career.%20If%20you%20stand%20up%20for%20your%20soldiers%20now%2C%20then%20it's%20going%20to%20have%20positive%20results%20later%2C%20even%20if%20it%20means%20putting%20your%20own%20neck%20out%20in%20the%20moment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bc097676-df2e-4e92-95da-308c425eef31%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFiguring%20out%20the%20system%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221366%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Cathrine%20Schmid%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6650b92620abc1efe8fd6c14%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221329%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESchmid%20participating%20in%20the%20Army%20Combat%20Fitness%20Test%20in%20December%202023%3Cp%3EPhoto%20courtesy%20of%20Cathrine%20Schmid%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20stationed%20in%20Tampa%2C%20Florida.%20The%20queer%20community%20down%20there%2C%20at%20least%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20was%20very%20strong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20discovered%20the%20organization%20SPARTA%20in%20the%20spring%20of%202014%2C%20which%20came%20out%20of%20all%20of%20the%20people%20who%20were%20in%20the%20organization%20OutServe%20back%20in%20the%20day%20when%20Don't%20Ask%20Don't%20Tell%2C%20the%20discriminatory%20prohibition%20on%20gay%20and%20lesbian%20service%20members%2C%20was%20repealed%20and%20wanted%20to%20begin%20fighting%20for%20open%20transgender%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20people%20formed%20their%20own%20splinter%20organization%20less%20than%20a%20year%20before%20I%20came%20out.%20I%20found%20a%20community%2C%20and%20I%20found%20mentors%20and%20friends.%20I%20ended%20up%20meeting%20my%20now-spouse%20through%20one%20of%20the%20local%20queer%20groups%20there%20in%20Florida.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20and%20I%20got%20married%20right%20after%20Obergefell%20v.%20Hodges%2C%20which%20legalized%20same-sex%20marriage%2C%20in%20August%202015%20because%20we%20had%20no%20idea%20whether%20it%20was%20going%20to%20stick.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20October%202016%2C%20the%20Army%20had%20procedures%20in%20place%20to%20get%20our%20gender%20marker%20changed%20in%20DEERS%20or%20Defense%20Enrollment%20Eligibility%20Reporting%20System%2C%20a%20large%20database%20for%20service%20member%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20finished%20the%20medical%20portion%20of%20my%20transition%2C%20specifically%20I%20was%20able%20to%20get%20surgery%2C%20two%20years%20later%20in%202018%2C%20and%20I%20had%20a%20unit%20that%20was%20supportive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20a%20benefit%20to%20the%20mission%2C%20and%20it%20is%20going%20to%20get%20accomplished%20better%20with%20you%20than%20without%20you%2C%20then%20nothing%20else%20really%20matters.%20That's%20the%20reason%20I%20kept%20re-enlisting%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20The%20mission%20is%20something%20that's%20meaningful%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2252d15ca7-2db6-456c-97b9-81c451ed2104%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENow%20what%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20I%20was%20stationed%20in%20Washington%2C%20and%20our%20morning%20formation%20was%20always%206%3A30%20a.m.%20About%2015%20minutes%20before%20I%20was%20supposed%20to%20stand%20in%20formation%20and%20salute%20the%20flag%2C%20my%20phone%20started%20blowing%20up%20with%20people%20texting%20me%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%2C%20did%20you%20see%20this%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20phone%20just%20started%20exploding.%20The%20commander-in-chief%20had%20put%20out%20a%20new%20policy%20via%20Twitter%20that%20would%20place%20a%20ban%20on%20transgender%20military%20personnel%2C%20affecting%20thousands%20of%20service%20members%20throughout%20the%20country.%20And%20my%20immediate%20reaction%20was%2C%20%26quot%3BWell%20now%20what%20do%20I%20do%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20thought%20back%20to%20Col.%20Cammermayer%20who%20was%20an%20Army%20nurse%20back%20in%20Vietnam%20and%20made%20it%20all%20the%20way%20to%20colonel.%20To%20get%20promoted%20to%20general%2C%20she%20had%20to%20have%20her%20security%20clearance%20reviewed.%20She%20admitted%20to%20being%20lesbian%2C%20so%20she%20got%20discharged%20from%20the%20Army%2C%20but%20then%20successfully%20fought%20it%20and%20got%20reinstated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20was%20one%20of%20the%20very%20few%20out%2C%20non-straight%20people%20in%20the%20military%2C%20but%20she%20was%20able%20to%20finish%20her%20career%20on%20her%20terms.%20Her%20story%20kept%20ringing%20in%20my%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20the%20Army%20Service%20lead%20for%20SPARTA%2C%20and%20one%20person%20on%20the%20board%20reached%20out%20and%20said%20Lambda%20Legal%20is%20putting%20together%20a%20lawsuit.%20They%20represented%20Cammermayer%20back%20in%20the%20day%20as%20well%2C%20so%20I%20gave%20them%20my%20name.%20I%20have%20the%20distinction%20of%20being%20one%20of%20very%20few%20active-duty%20service%20members%20who%20have%20su