2C%20but%20I%20also%20dislike%20the%20transactional%20nature%20of%20doing%20chores%20strictly%20to%20get%20money.%20I%20want%20my%20kids%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmoney-lessons-millionaire-retiree-taught-her-kids-2021-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Elearn%20to%20contribute%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20the%20family's%20well-being.%20In%20return%20for%20doing%20so%2C%20I'm%20happy%20to%20support%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20think%20of%20it%20as%20more%20of%20a%20salary%20approach%20to%20allowance%20than%20paying%20kids%20for%20specific%20chores.%20I%20pay%20for%20the%20things%20they%20need%2C%20like%20clothes%20when%20they%20outgrew%20the%20previous%20size%2C%20but%20they%20pay%20for%20wants%2C%20like%20trendy%20new%20sneakers.%20I%20distribute%20money%20monthly%20%E2%80%94%20they%20get%20a%20dollar%20a%20week%20for%20each%20year%20of%20their%20age%20%E2%80%94%20as%20long%20as%20the%20kids%20are%20doing%20things%20around%20the%20house%20as%20needed.%20There%20have%20been%20times%20when%20the%20household%20to-dos%20aren't%20done%2C%20so%20I%20hold%20back%20their%20allowance.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22158d44b0-4ace-4672-8fc5-f91b452447b9%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20reward%20problem-solving%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESometimes%2C%20the%20kids%20need%20or%20want%20extra%20money.%20They%20have%20to%20earn%20it%2C%20which%20they%20do%20most%20often%20by%20completing%20extra%20chores%20around%20the%20house%20that%20pay%20out%20immediately.%20For%20example%2C%20one%20of%20my%20daughters%20once%20noted%20our%20doors%20were%20squeaking%2C%20so%20she%20asked%20if%20I%20would%20pay%20her%20to%20fix%20them.%20I%20was%20happy%20to%20hand%20over%20the%20WD-40%20%E2%80%94%20as%20well%20as%20the%20money%2C%20once%20the%20job%20was%20done.%20We%20agree%20on%20the%20amount%20before%20the%20job%20starts%2C%20often%20%2410%20or%20%2420%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20amount%20of%20work.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20want%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillionaire-parent-teaches-kids-budgeting-entitlement-stability-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eteach%20my%20kids%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20they%20won't%20get%20something%20just%20because%20they%20ask.%20Instead%2C%20I%20reward%20them%20for%20their%20ingenuity%20in%20spotting%20a%20problem%2C%20brainstorming%20a%20solution%2C%20and%20proposing%20a%20service.%20That's%20a%20lot%20more%20reflective%20of%20how%20life%20really%20works.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228fa18553-54c0-47b6-a098-288c48aba469%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20taught%20the%20three%20uses%20of%20money%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20of%20my%20most%20frequent%20dad-isms%20is%20about%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fentrepreneur-mom-money-lessons-kids-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethree%20uses%20of%20money%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%20giving%2C%20saving%2C%20and%20spending.%20I%20try%20to%20emphasize%20them%20in%20that%20order.%20The%20kids%20have%20always%20been%20taught%20to%20do%20all%20three.%20I%20don't%20give%20them%20specific%20percentages%20to%20aim%20for%20because%20I%20want%20to%20emphasize%20the%20principle%20and%20help%20them%20learn%20the%20lesson%20rather%20than%20just%20have%20them%20check%20a%20box%20on%20a%20to-do%20list%20for%20allocating%20a%20specific%20amount%20toward%20a%20specific%20bucket.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOnce%2C%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20my%20then-11-year-old%20daughter%20found%20a%20%2420%20bill%20in%20the%20park.%20She%20was%20excited%20but%20flustered%3A%20she%20didn't%20know%20how%20she%20could%20split%20one%20bill%20into%20the%20three%20uses.%20I%20taught%20her%20how%20to%20get%20change%2C%20and%20she%20later%20handed%20%2410%20to%20a%20homeless%20person.%20I%20was%20so%20proud%20that%20she%20had%20internalized%20our%20family%20values%20about%20giving.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fa675fc3-24e5-4083-a838-bf37a5f98e9a%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20relate%20money%20to%20the%20real%20world%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMoney%20can%20be%20very%20abstract%2C%20so%20I've%20always%20tried%20to%20tie%20it%20into%20my%20kids'%20daily%20actions.%20We%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinancial-advice-from-baby-boomer-parents-for-gen-z-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eopened%20bank%20accounts%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20when%20the%20kids%20were%205%2C%20and%20got%20them%20debit%20cards%20when%20they%20were%20preteens.%20If%20I%20took%20my%20daughter%20shoe%20shopping%2C%20I%20would%20have%20her%20use%20her%20own%20card.%20Swiping%20the%20card%2C%20putting%20in%20the%20PIN%2C%20and%20later%20seeing%20the%20transaction%20on%20the%20banking%20app%20reinforced%20the%20idea%20that%20money%20was%20actually%20changing%20hands.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20did%20the%20same%20with%20investing.%20I%20encouraged%20them%20to%20look%20around%20their%20daily%20lives%20and%20notice%20what%20products%20they%20were%20using%20or%20what%20entertainment%20they%20enjoyed.%20I%20explained%20that%20businesses%20were%20behind%20all%20of%20that%2C%20and%20I%20taught%20them%20that%2C%20as%20shareholders%2C%20they%20could%20own%20a%20small%20piece%20of%20those%20companies.%20My%20kids%20have%20invested%20their%20allowance%20and%20money%20from%20their%20jobs%20outside%20the%20home%20in%20various%20companies%2C%20from%20Tesla%20when%20they%20were%20interested%20in%20electric%20vehicles%20to%20Disney%2B%20because%20of%20their%20affinity%20for%20Disney%20films.%20Investing%20in%20what%20they%20know%20and%20use%20makes%20it%20more%20tangible.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2278bbd95c-b54b-4fc